          "description": "Dr. Lee is a great surgeon! He answered all of my questions I had before my surgery. I broke my pinkie and he acted very quickly. First surgery went well and the recovery was exactly how he explained it.\n\nWe were suppose to have 2 surgeries but we ended up not needing to do a 2nd surgery to remove my pin since it was sticking out. The visits felt very genuine and I felt comfortable trusting their expertise.\n\nOnly complaint I have is that the nurse gave me instructions too soon post-surgery when I was still loopy. I missed some important information because I wasn\u2019t in the right state to listen. That caused me to suffer in more pain during day 1 and 2 without knowing how much more pain medicine I could take.",
